<subSubSection id="C7A4F5ECFFC7FF87CDB71C08FDEB11D4" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8F01A667FFC7FF87CDB71C08FDEB11D4" blockId="8.[185,1544,381,2079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
DIFFERENTIAL DIAGNOSIS. — The prominent yellow dorsal stripe, stout pyramidal process on the dorsum of the tenth abdominal segment and distinctly hooked-shaped posterior hamulus will serve to separate this 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CE161C6BFBF1128C" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[894,1060,1405,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CE161C6BFBF1128C" box="[894,1060,1405,1439]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Macromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other known species. There are no Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CF651CB8FD6712C3" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[525,690,1454,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CF651CB8FD6712C3" box="[525,690,1454,1488]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Macromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which are closely related to this new species. In neighbouring Vietnam, 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CCB61CF6FCEF1111" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[478,826,1504,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CCB61CF6FD7F1111" box="[478,682,1504,1538]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">M. cingulata</emphasis>
Rambur
</taxonomicName>
, also known from India and Nepal, although smaller, has similar body coloration, tenth abdominal process and hooked posterior hamulus. The posterior hamulus of 
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CFD61F55FCA31176" box="[702,886,1603,1637]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CFD61F55FC871176" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[702,850,1603,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cingulata">cingulata</taxonomicName>
is
</emphasis>
not so profoundly hooked as 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87C8291F55FA591176" authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[1345,1420,1603,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unca" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87C8291F55FA591176" box="[1345,1420,1603,1637]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">unca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the lateral teeth of the superior appendages are distal to the mid-point (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EB2FDB96FFC7FF87C86A1F62FE9111D4" author="FRASER, F. C." journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" refId="ref5191" refString="FRASER, F. C., 1936. Fauna o fBritish India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata, Vol 3, Taylor &amp; Francis, London." title="Fauna o fBritish India, including Ceylon and Burma. Odonata, Vol 3" type="book" year="1936">FRASER, 1936: 179-182</bibRefCitation>
, figs 57 &amp; 60c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C7A4F5ECFFC7FF87CD881FCCFE8A1F0C" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8F01A667FFC7FF87CD881FCCFE8A1F0C" blockId="8.[185,1544,381,2079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
REMARKS. — Following the publication of the 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CE821FC0FBA411EB" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[1002,1137,1750,1784]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Odonata</taxonomicName>
of Hainan (
<bibRefCitation id="EB2FDB96FFC7FF87C8521FC0FE49103A" author="WILSON, K. D. P. &amp; G. T. REELS" journalOrPublisher="Odonatologica" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" pagination="145 - 208" part="30" refId="ref5512" refString="WILSON, K. D. P. &amp; G. T. REELS, 2001. Odonata of Hainan, China. Odonatologica 30 (2): 145 - 208." title="Odonata of Hainan, China" type="journal article" year="2001">
WILSON &amp; 
<collectionCode id="E9AF3EA2FFC7FF87CDD61E11FEEF103A" box="[190,314,1799,1833]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">REELS</collectionCode>
, 2001
</bibRefCitation>
) there were 16 species of 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CE521E11FC35103A" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[826,992,1799,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CE521E11FC35103A" box="[826,992,1799,1833]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Macromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from Chinese territory. Including 
<taxonomicName id="48BEDDE4FFC7FF87CC571E2EFE5F1049" authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[319,394,1848,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Corduliidae" genus="Macromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unca" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BDCA7A75FFC7FF87CC571E2EFE5F1049" box="[319,394,1848,1882]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">unca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are now 17 species known from China. The four females and two males were taken on two successive evenings, just before dusk, in a shaded lane adjacent to a Forestry Department field station. No observations of this species were made, during day light for the entire period of the two-week survey conducted in the Shikengkong area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
